text: this past saturday, i was able to take part in shooting a pilot for a show where the producers believe that every comedian cast is talented (funny) enough to close out any show out there.  the tour bus was dope!!! omg, wow- this was part of the dream, to be sure. our promo poster said “pound me too tour” and several of us got some pretty heated messages in our dm’s over it. it’s kind of sad because if anyone should be able to laugh and poke fun, shouldn’t it be women who share #metoo stories? - but- also, does that hate mail mean i’m getting more popular? 😃 i think the tour name is hilarious, and i’m so honored and flattered that i was chosen to be a part of this production. thank you @lahnaturnerr for this opportunity, and to @sallymullins818 @gaylaevent @outoftheboxrosie for the wonderful memories!  and yes, if your wondering, every comedian killed. 💗 #standup #standupcomedy #love #femalecomedian #womencomedians #metoo #saggyballranch
name: Melanie Baldonado

text:
this past week i came forward about being sexually assaulted by two of my brothers friends and raped by one of my friends in high school. i described how okay i am and how i only want to share anything as a means of helping others in a similar situation and by no means want to come for the people who did it to me, as i don't feel as though they are innately bad people. i described why i didn't feel safe telling my family due to years of not having a stable relationship, being abused, and never trusted as a kid. how i let the threats of my attackers have control over me. how i felt like they wouldn't care or believe me and how i felt like i simply didn't have a voice as a teenager. after years of them making fun of sexual assault victims, i decided to stop standing by and letting them unknowingly hurt me. 
after my mom and brother found out, i was called a liar and a cunt after being told that the rape was not as big of a deal because they didn't know him as much as my brothers friends and that was more damaging to their egos. i was made to feel like the guilt i made them feel for not being able to tell them was more important than how they made me feel. i was told the mental health issues i struggle with aren't real. i was told that forgiveness is not real and that i am absolutely insane to come out and say after 8-10 years that i forgive my atrackers and have allowed myself to continue living, but not in the shadow of what has happened to me - because those stories aren't defining of who i am as a person, although they made me stronger.
i want to make an appreciation post for all of the people who are strong enough to come forward with their stories as well as an appreciation post for all of the people who have heard their loved ones open up about something so embarrassing, difficult, and painful and been supportive and loving. i want to not forget how many good people there are still in the world that i am so grateful for.
although this justified why i never felt comfortable coming forward to them, i want to express to everyone how important it is to not hold onto those secrets that kill you inside for the sake of not...

text: #cyntoiabrown (my first pic was suppose to be a picture of her getting an early release date but i messed that up. i wanted to post her first bc she’s an example of what abuse can do)  i see a lot of us don’t have a clear understanding of what abuse is, the types of abuse and the extreme power that abuse has. it is a confusing topic with so many layers to it... but between cyntoia brown & r kelly i’m happy it’s being discussed. i urge people to stop arguing about it, stop blaming, shaming and pointing fingers esp at survivors and really get educated just in order to really help to stop the cycle. this social media platform is so dangerous in the wrong hands. someone you love and know may be going through it and you wouldn’t know, they may not even fully understand it themselves in order to express it. someone who follows you may have decided to tell someone today and a post you make may have them thinking it’s their fault. someone you know may also be an abuser, & when you blame or shame the survivor you are feeding the ego and psyche of the abuser. a lot of victims love their abuser and think their abuser loves them & will never tell bc oftentimes they also blame themselves for what they may not fully understand. that’s what abuse does. victim shaming/blaming has always been a thing and it keeps the abused silent and that’s also a form of abuse. it also turns the abuser into the victim which feeds their inner beast. stop doing that... it’s ignorant. don’t be a part of the problem... please! 💜 #metoo
name: R. Jackson/Skylar's Mom💜

text: juxtaposing all this surviving mr. r&b controversy against the reality of cyntoia brown, i ask that we focus more of our attention to our own locus of control in fighting #whitesupremacistcapitalistpatriarchy which is often #imo the #sideeffect of #toxicmasculinity that results in daily racial and gender privileges not only imbedded in all our systems--especially political--but even in our movements which unremorsefully perpetuate the stifling of victims and the persistent attack on black bodies both male, female, transgendered, and religious. we each have a power and agency in acting to do one thing in our environment, to do more for other populations that intersect our identity. while cyntoia has been granted clemency, she has not found justice...just like the unnamed 14 year old girl in the lifetime docuseries or other women and men living with the scars of their childhood. #metoo often seems like #notustoo and well #alllivesmatter only when we talk about #blacklives abused both in the street and on college campuses or at the expense of privilege and capitalism. so this longwinded soap box is to #challenge you #daily to ask yourself what can "i" do in this space to help someone in need, and more importantly...#act. #dailyequitydeposits #bebetterdobetter2019 #drconeysoapbox #itneveriswhatitis #itswhatumakeit ✊🏾 #stopenablingbullshit #weencouragewhatwetolerate 🗣

text:
awesome news!!!! “gov. bill haslam granted brown clemency on monday. she will be released to parole supervision on aug. 7, 2019, after serving 15 years in prison, according to the announcement from haslam's office. “ “thank you, governor haslam, for your act of mercy in giving me a second chance.  i will do everything i can to justify your faith in me. 
i want to thank those at the tennessee department of corrections who saw something in me worth salvaging, especially ms. connie seabrooks for allowing me to participate in the lipscomb life program. it changed my life.  i am also grateful to those at the tennessee department of corrections who will work with me over the next several months to help me in the transition from prison to the free world. 
thank you to dr. richard goode and dr. kate watkins and all of you at lipscomb university for opening up a whole new world for me. i have one course left to finish my bachelor’s degree, which i will complete in may 2019.
i am thankful for all the support, prayers, and encouragement i have received. we truly serve a god of second chances and new beginnings.  the lord has held my hand this whole time and i would have never made it without him.  let today be a testament to his saving grace. 
thank you to my family for being a backbone these past 14 years. 
i am thankful to my lawyers and their staffs, and all the others who, for the last decade have freely given of their time and expertise to help me get to this day. 
i love all of you and will be forever grateful.
with god’s help, i am committed to live the rest of my life helping others, especially young people.  my hope is to help other young girls avoid ending up where i have been. 
thank you.”
. .

question:
are you following the pearl: blog yet?
.
the pearl project as a whole sets a theme for every month that each one of our projects focus on.
.
for example, january’s theme is “relationships,” and so at our pearl: book clubs and at the pearl: soirée gatherings, our pearl ladies are having intentional chats about alllll things #relationships
.
the pearl: blog follows suit by offering a faith-based perspective on various facets of our most meaningful relationships.
.
don’t worry, your inbox won’t get overloaded. we shoot out one blog post per month because well, you’re busy and we are busy and we’re all about quality versus quantity.
.
so if you’re someone who appreciates hearing varying perspectives on things like relationships and sexuality and culture and faith, message us your email address so that we can add you to our pearl: blog email list.
.
p.s
if you’d like to be considered for being one of our write-in bloggers please let us know! .
thanks + blessings!
- @jenna__hays
.

text:
réalisatrice en dernière année de l’ecole de la cité, je suis très activement à la recherche d’un ou une producteur.rice pour m’accompagner dans la concrétisation de mon court métrage de fin d’études.

ce projet est un conte médiéval et féministe de 15 minutes, racontant l’histoire d’un clan de bohémiennes séquestrées dans un château fort et luttant pour leur liberté. 
il s’inspire de deux chefs-d’oeuvres de la tragédie : l’opéra carmen de bizet, et notre-dame de paris de victor hugo. 
a travers ce projet ambitieux sur son message, son univers et son esthétique, je souhaite évoquer des thèmes qui me tiennent résolument à coeur : le besoin de liberté, l’amour de soi-même & la monstruosité.

le projet compte déjà à son bord deux merveilleuses collaboratrices : la chef opératrice @naomiamarger (dernière année de louis lumière) et la charismatique et talentueuse @julietteboucheny dans le rôle principal.

text:
finished. what a powerful piece for me. it was about both letting go of something really dear and important to me, and also gaining strength through the process. someone asked me who the figures are… they were and are, originally, both different sides of myself, and identity. but while painting, it also turned into a historical piece, one of strength, resilience, and resistance. the women aren’t me at all. they’re everywoman, all of us, and the human experience. they’re the women who marched for the right to vote. the women who ended segregation. the women who said #metoo with strength, the women who go in front of the world in protest to injustice, to stop another man from assuming so much power. these are the women of the future. it’s a painting of hope for a better world for us all. one that will, if we’re successful, be guided by women. women are our hope and our strength. -
-
-

take a moment to read my thoughts: i boycotted r. kelleys music in 2002 when i saw the video ~ i know it was him. clearly.  i wasn’t comfortable talking about it because the world i lived in .... everyone thought it was a joke, and they made me feel ike i was too earnest. i saw the bbc documentary, i read the buzz feed and new yorker articles ... as a #survivor and a black woman in the music industry, i just broke down sobbing when i saw the video. i sobbed, because it was a graphic illustration, that i lived in a world that didnt value people like me. and i had to learn to take care of myself in the face of a society and industry that doesn’t love me. i learned that i had to wear the crown of my ancestors and hold my own head up. and its been hard. but i do it because i believe in my mission ~ i don’t need to sing about the fight , my mission is to administer to the people in the fight. humanity makes me sad all the time ~ the things were going thru ... but also today, i’m hopeful, that we as a group are now #muterkelly ~ but, i wont be satisfied until every abused person knows, that “everyone of us is worthy” and when ever someone treats us as less, that is thier mistake, ... and while the wound is not our doing, it is our responsibility ~ we have to heal ourselves.  that healing can take on so much more momentum, when the world around us is healing too.... so i feel good today knowing that we as a collective are waking up even more, to the ways that the world / the music industry / the society / the culture ~ harm our women and girls.  and! i feel good today knowing that these growing pains are about growth. we are all! worthy and significant and we matter! because we exist!  may we keep waking up to that fact. it is a fact! everyone of us is #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #worthy #survivingrkelly #iamlight #muterkelly #survivingrkelly #rkelly #blackgirlsmatter #metoo

text:
okay ladies i’m about to go on a rant:

we have fought to have body shaming recognized, #metoo, bullying and equality and yet woman bashing woman is so common we just fluff past it. 
well stop 🛑 it!!! today in the grocery store there was a beautiful younger woman shopping (just shopping), when 2 women started to make comments loud enough that the beautiful woman would hear and others in the area...”doesn’t she think she’s all that”...”how much did that face cost”...”she’s lucky to look like that because obviously that’s all she has”...” i wonder what she charges” and several other statements.

of course this hurt the woman...you could see it on her face as the other woman laughed and moved on. i approached her and asked if she was ok...her reply was all to familiar “yeah you get used to it” omg seriously how can one get used to that. i told her she was a stunning lady and to hold her head high and shine and never allow others insecurities or jealousy to steal her thunder.

i walked out remembering how just a few weeks earlier at my pop up event a group of women had done the same thing to me. they intentionally were cruel, hurtful and bullied me with the intention of humiliating me. i was hurt and degraded all because it made them feel better about who they were. i remembered saying that evening “yeah it hurts like crazy but you get used to it”

bullshit!!! you don’t get used to it!!! no one gets used to it and nor should they. like this woman today i walked away holding my head high not allowing them to see me cry. i’m sure i will face this again and i pray i have the strength to carry myself with the same dignity i was raised to have.

my point of this is to say ladies how can we demand respect, kindness and understanding from others when just because another women feels like a threat to our egos we bash her. so please before you jump to conclusions or form an opinion on nothing more than appearance stop 🛑 and ask if you would want someone to do that to you!!! sorry gang this one just hit home today and no one deserves to be treated that way!!! #bullying #meangirls #jealous #stopit #meanwomen #buildup
name: Annette Pitcher

text:
«a la base un collage made in ©️hervé malgorn.
des gants de boxe fleuris façon 70’s avec le texte en dessous « dites lui avec des fleurs », selon la jolie formule romantique...pour parler avec les dents qui grincent du tabassage quasi quotidien « en bonne et due forme » d’une femme, compagne, amante sur quatre, par des connards de bonhommes qui n’ont d’homme que la pauvre petite bite entre leurs cuisses de merde, et rien d’autre.
(bien entendu parmi les hommes qui lisent ça, un certain nombre sont pratiquants. ben tu sais quoi mon gars, mes voeux pour 2019 reçois les à coups de barre à mine dans ta sale gueule de faux-cul. bisous connard.)
puis le collage est devenu par la grâce des talents de brodeuse de @ca_la_mi_ty aka 💕jen moret💕 une broderie contemporaine, troc entre artistes ouais t’as vu ! ⭐️👌🏻⭐️
tout ceci pour vous dire et vous prévenir que l’expo que je prépare en collab’ avec l’artiste @31novembre aka catherine arbassette pour le mois de mai sera punchy et pour ma part violente vis-à-vis de nous tous et de nos incohérences de putes, et vis-à-vis des merdes à bites sur pattes en particulier.
💋joyeux noël 💋
des bises 😬👻😬👻😬 🇺🇸 🇬🇧 👉🏻 for the bitches who don’t even speak french « dites lui avec des fleurs » means « say it to her with flowers », a romantic french expression...here to speak about violences against women... »
bordeaux saint-michel.
janvier 2019.
.
.
.

text:
hey 👋 i've been working on some illustrations for @chaynhq, really excited to share a sneak peak with you. they're doing some really great stuff - check it out.
....................................................
since last year, we've been working on an intersectional guide for survivors on how to deal with #mentalhealth and #wellbeing challenges. if you are in or have been in an abusive relationship, you know what we are talking about. feeling like spinning out of control. feeling low. feeling anxious. triggers. panic attacks. unexplainable feelings. feeling lost and alone. many of us have been through it. 
so this is why we need your help in seeing if our new guide would have been useful when you felt like that or feels useful now? you do not need to be a therapist or psychologist but if you are, please help us too! we will keep comments open until saturday, 12 january. click on the link in the @chaynhq bio to add your feedback! irrespective of whether you help us make this better or not, we just want to say we see you. we hear you. we are with you. you matter. your feelings matter. 
_

#chayn #chaynhq #womenintech #strongtogether #metoo #techforgood #opensource #girlpower #womenempowerment #domesticviolence #genderequality #feminism ⠀

text:
(cnn) cyntoia denise brown, a woman serving a life sentence for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16 years old, has been granted clemency, the tennessee governor's office said monday.

brown, 30, will be released to parole supervision on august 7 after serving 15 years in prison, gov. bill haslam's office said in a statement. "this decision comes after careful consideration of what is a tragic and complex case," haslam said.

#cyntoiabrown committed, by her own admission, a horrific crime at the age of 16. yet, imposing a life sentence on a juvenile that would require her to serve at least 51 years before even being eligible for parole consideration is too harsh, especially in light of the extraordinary steps ms. brown has taken to rebuild her life. transformation should be accompanied by hope." brown's case drew the attention of several high-profile advocates including a us congressman, several tennessee lawmakers and a number of a-list celebrities. comedian amy schumer, reality star #kimkardashianwest, #rihanna and actress #ashleyjudd were among those who called for brown's clemency.

text:
sunshine on a cloudy day☀️
.
felt honored to spend a few days in jerusalem, learning about the complexity surrounding the politics and disputes over holy sites and territory. after 18 hours of listening to one of the most knowledgeable tour guides in jerusalem, i learned that my knowledge of this place is a thimble in a sea of history. i can’t pretend to have any idea what should happen to resolve the debate, so i won’t.
.
i will say that i met people who were kind, generous and hospitable on both sides. who disagreed with one another but still laughed and shared turkish coffee and home rolled tobacco cigs at the end of the day.
.
i left with two pressing thoughts:
first, i pray for peace. for jerusalem to be free from bickering and noise, but also for america’s chaos to quiet.
.
second, i saw people divided on every topic imaginable (race, ethnicity, religion, politics, ancestry) disagree politely but still respect and honor one another. to those in jerusalem who held the banner of honor for humanity high, thank you. you have taught me a lesson that will forever remain imprinted in my heart.
.
we are only as strong as as we are united, as weak as we are divided.
name: ✨եɾɑѵҽӀ & ɑժѵҽղեմɾҽ

text:
(cnn) cyntoia denise brown, a woman serving a life sentence for killing a man who bought her for sex when she was 16 years old, has been granted clemency, the tennessee governor's office said monday.

brown, 30, will be released to parole supervision on august 7 after serving 15 years in prison, gov. bill haslam's office said in a statement. "this decision comes after careful consideration of what is a tragic and complex case," haslam said.

#cyntoiabrown committed, by her own admission, a horrific crime at the age of 16. yet, imposing a life sentence on a juvenile that would require her to serve at least 51 years before even being eligible for parole consideration is too harsh, especially in light of the extraordinary steps ms. brown has taken to rebuild her life. transformation should be accompanied by hope." brown's case drew the attention of several high-profile advocates including a us congressman, several tennessee lawmakers and a number of a-list celebrities. comedian amy schumer, reality star #kimkardashianwest, #rihanna and actress #ashleyjudd were among those who called for brown's clemency.

text:
😬 it’s a tough topic to discuss but a very important one nevertheless. 😡 so here we go! 👉 #metoo movement is bleeding out with stories of misuse of sexual energy. doors of shame are being broken down to let light and healing in. it's time for a new understanding. 👉 many of us don’t understand how sexual energy actually works because it's been hidden under a lot of pain, shame and poor sexual education. 👉 it’s common to think of sex when you hear the words sexual energy. you might even think of the charge that exists between two people who are seriously attracted to each other. i want to bust some myths and help you understand that it is so much more. 👉 sexual energy can be used like a pen, either to stab someone, or to write a beautiful poem. there is nothing wrong with the pen, but it’s how you choose to use it. you use it based on how you’ve seen and have been taught to use it. 👉 the reason i personally got interested in the topic of sexual energy is because as a high achieving super woman i burnt out and with it, i lost my sexual energy. i got sick, physically, mentally and emotionally. i lost my sparkle which harshly affected my personal and my professional life. in search for answers to these questions: what is sexual energy, where did it go, how does it actually work and most importantly how do i get it back, what i found forever rocked my world. 😮

if you're open to it, i'm here to show you a different view of sexual energy and it’s uses for health, wealth and charisma. 👇 read full article here: http://bit.ly/2vijxm2

text:
i sat and watched all of #survivingrkelly last night and the early hours of this morning. having been aware of the stories of these courageous women for years i stopped listening to him a long time ago. r kelly was a part of the soundtrack of my teenage years but this is no loss because i stand with these women. the victims. the survivors. all women that have been and lived and triumphed through these horrific experiences. i carry mine with me, as i know they do, every single day and i work, every single day, to move further and further away from that scared little girl. i've always avoided the word survivor but watching those women last night, i get it. this is my offering to them and to everyone else that understands. this was hard to write and i think i've given myself a headache in the process but sometimes you do just have to bleed on the page. 
i whisper for those not yet able to speak
i speak for those not yet able to scream
i scream for myself until my throat is bloody
i'll spit that blood down on to this
scorched earth and watch as
warriors grow from my
blood and my pain and my strength.
they, too, will scream until they split and bleed
spilling our blood magic further still.
so, we scream and bleed together as we
create more and more of us from this
damaged and broken beginning.
we will scream until eardrums shatter and bust
and until the world is silent.
we will scream for ourselves
until you shut up and listen.
we will scream for each other
until we are all finally heard.
i. will. scream.

text: [lundinspiration] a la genèse, il y a une réflexion basique sur « avec quoi rime 2019 ? ». quand ça finit par te sauter aux yeux, tu creuses. 2018, une année de #metoo certes, mais aussi une année de multiplication des comptes instagram invitant les femmes à reprendre le contrôle de leur vie, de leur corps, de leur choix. pourtant le feminism bashing continue. des hommes et des femmes disent qu’ils ne sont pas « féministes » comme si ce mot était une tare. en commençant ce compte et cette année 2019 par une courte vidéo de #beyonce (#flawless), c’est un message à la « le féminisme pour les nuls » que je voulais vous passer. tout d’abord, à l’image de queen b, il existe des centaines de façon d’être féministe. loin du cliché de la féminazi, chacun et chacune peut prendre sa part, à son rythme, selon ses moyens, pour faire évoluer les mentalités et faire progresser la société. et parce que la doctrine de base du féminisme est bien résumée par les paroles de cet extrait : « feminist : a person who believes in the social, political and economic equality of the sexes ». alors ensemble, reprenons les bases et montrons que oui, le féminisme est un engagement auquel tout le monde a envie d’adhérer.
name: 2019 année de la meuf

day 92:
the 35th president of the united states of america. john fitzgerald “jack” kennedy was a president who lasted two years due to his assassination in 1963. he was assassinated by former u.s marine, lee harvey oswald. at the time, the government claimed that oswald acted alone, but conspiracy theorists don’t believe this. this is due to the fact that he  managed to fire three bullets in eight seconds from a bolt action rifle and that the second shot struck through the back and exited through the neck before hitting a second person in the back and exiting through the chest. also on top of that he managed to get onto a public transport bus after assassinating possibly the worlds most powerful man. other theories suggest it was lindsay johnson as a power grab so that he could become president which he did. some say it was the cubans like fidel castro as jfk and the c.i.a were trying to overthrow castro or even the mafia as jfk’s brother had started a crackdown on them. whilst others believe that oswald did in fact act alone since there has been no other ties to the assassination. also, his mental state was worse for wear as there is clear evidence that he also shot dead officer tippit an hour after jfk which would make him fit the profile of a psychopath. what do you think? did oswald act alone in the assassination of jfk or was there others behind the act?
credit: @_chris.exe_

text:
yo squad!! in light of #survivingrkelly. would you still support an artist accused of these allegations?... leave your opinion in the comments. start talking... (the music video may '08 was based on a true story, the faces and the names have been changed to protect the identity of a friend that confided in me. this story was so compelling and touching that i decided to shed light on the horrifying act that so many people go through. incest is a subject that affects every race and economic status all over the world. in the year of the #metoo movement where women are rightfully speaking up around the globe, i do encourage that we do not forget that sexual abuse and the loss of innocence can happen to any gender. incest is a reality that is hard to talk about and makes people feel ashamed and hurt. men and women have kept this secret taboo subject within themselves and their scars are forever  frozen in time.

hip hop is not about whose the best, it's about what you do when you have the mic. now it's my turn.

if you need some counseling or someone to speak with call: the national sexual assault hotline.
1-800-656-4673)

text:
i wrote this the other day as i was watching the #survivingrkelly documentary, it's amazing to me how many ppl victim shame these women with the amount of evidence they have against him. i was like that until it happened to me. i have been sexually, mentally, and physically abused...but i never came forward because i know how society is. my justice is getting up everyday, being able to give love, plan my future, and see myself as something more than a victim....i am a #survivor !

text:
do you ever buy yourself flowers. . . just because?  i love flowers and have for as long as i can remember.  i’ve always thought the right flower can have a positive impact - and while i now know it takes much more than flowers to make things better, a part of me still believes it is true.
.
when i saw these at the grocery store, i “needed” them!  not only are they pink (one of my fave colors), but to me tulips represent spring.  it is a nice reminder that spring will be here again someday 😊
.
the nice thing is that they are inexpensive - many grocery stores sell bunches of flowers for less than $5; they last about a week; they brighten the house; and they brighten my mood.  next time you are in a funk, or just because, get yourself a bouquet of flowers.  we don’t need to wait for someone to buy them for us.  enjoy! 🌷
name: Denise Styer, PsyD

this is the first book of it’s kind. the black man’s bible details a young black males struggles with the world, religions, drugs, crime, money and sex. throughout his life he studies advanced scholarly material which changes his view of the world over and over again as he matures. he battles health issues after he goes through a traumatic experience with the delivery of his first child. so he delivered his second son at home. the video of the home delivery can be seen at theblackmansbible.com. in the book he details how he finds himself in history repeatedly in different times periods. he also gives vivid descriptions of his experiences with love and women. then, after becoming an online entrepreneur, he travels to germany and china for free. he has struggles with finding a career and ends up becoming an author. he covers many subjects that are not popular to the modern day world. he has compiled a multitude of experiences that are dissected through the abstract different types of black males. this is the book of the century. the true guide for black males lost in the western world.

text:
i'm proud of the women that have come out to tell their stories on r. kelly. we need more of this. we need to have more open conversations on control. emotional and physical abuse are so incredibly prevalent in our society. sometimes it almost feels like it's almost accepted. r. kelly is an extreme example of abuse, but it's important to remember that abuse can also come in very small ways. when the abuse happens on either side (man or woman), it is not ok and it can not be justified. .
.
small things like: jealous comments, going through another person's personal property (phone, social media accounts included), silent treatments, or requests to modify behavior or dress - these things are not ok from both men or women. .
.
if your partner is easily angered, this needs to be addressed (not by you, but by a professional). if your partner is jealous, that is not a sign of love, it is an expression of control. if you are pressured into sex, it is not ok - you do not, ever, owe anyone for anything they do or give you. .
.
do not confuse control for love. never put a relationship with anyone before yourself. love yourself. take care of yourself. identify the red flags and if you see them, do not be afraid to walk away. you are not "giving up". you are not selfish or inconsiderate. you are choosing to put yourself first. valuing yourself and putting yourself first is the most loving and considerate thing you can do in any relationship. .
.
finally, remember that people love you and that you can ask for help. that doesn't make you weak. it's makes you the strongest person on this planet. #metoo #muterkelly #elmachismomata

this is the first book of it’s kind. the black man’s bible details a young black males struggles with the world, religions, drugs, crime, money and sex. throughout his life he studies advanced scholarly material which changes his view of the world over and over again as he matures. he battles health issues after he goes through a traumatic experience with the delivery of his first child. so he delivered his second son at home. the video of the home delivery can be seen at theblackmansbible.com. in the book he details how he finds himself in history repeatedly in different times periods. he also gives vivid descriptions of his experiences with love and women. then, after becoming an online entrepreneur, he travels to germany and china for free. he has struggles with finding a career and ends up becoming an author. he covers many subjects that are not popular to the modern day world. he has compiled a multitude of experiences that are dissected through the abstract different types of black males. this is the book of the century. the true guide for black males lost in the western world.

text:
happy motivation monday!

h.o.p.e.... hope is the only thing more powerful than fear. we all experience pain, it’s a part of life. as with absolutely everything in life, nothing lasts forever. 
whatever you are going through, whatever the scale of your pain, keep hope in mind because at some point the pain will end.
i have lots of experience with this, especially since 2016. i am still in so much pain, and when i look back, i am realizing that ever so slightly, the physical, mental and soulful pain is starting to get better... and i hold on to the hope that one day the pain will end. i hope the same for everyone reading this who is in pain 💕
.
.
.

text_retweet: in times of chaos, sometimes i lose hope. i almost lost hope for this case until i saw @denearjoseph reposts and reshares over and over again to help this woman along with other prominent activists such as @snaybelle and @shaunking. i signed two petitions after seeing their strength and perseverance. sometimes you get burned out from all the pain that injustice can bring. sometimes i need to remove myself completely from it until i find the strength again. sometimes it feels like no matter how hard you fight, injustice and evil will always prevail. however, i like to believe this is a new era of change and was so happy to find out that cyntoia was granted clemency by governor bill haslam. her release is set for august 7, 2019. i ask god to keep her alive and safe until then and for the system to release all other similar cases like hers. i put quotations and added a d to this picture because although she is set to be released/freed, we must also acknowledge that she shouldn’t have been locked up in the first place. -bon 🧡

text:
hawaii’s house of representatives has revamped its sexual harassment policy, a result of pressures brought on by the #metoo movement and resignation of house speaker joe souki last year.

the new policy includes revised definitions of sexual harassment, clarifies reporting procedures for filing a complaint, prohibits retaliation against someone who files a complaint and requires annual training for all house members and employees, among other changes.

do you think the changes will help?

text:
rest in the unknown. —
it’s been awhile since i have shared anything. i’ve been in and out of doctor appointments trying to find answers to my migraines that i had been dealing with since april 2017. along with the migraines i’ve also been dealing with blurred vision. i went to the optometrist to get my eyes checked out. so back to the doctor for more answers to find the root to my physical pain which has left me in bed for weeks at a time and housebound. —
i finally have the answers to my migraines and blurred vision. which has brought along much anxiety and a lot of emotional pain of reliving my #metoo story. i have been going to a counselor rehashing my nightmare. for months i had thought what happened to me was my fault. having my head slammed against a wall by my ex-boyfriend who also made me believe that i was going crazy when money would go missing or when my newly bought ipad pro had mysteriously disappeared. since i didn’t have health insurance at the time i didn’t go to the doctor and also because i was manipulated into believing that if i did go to the doctor they would have to file a report and this would have prevented my ex from being a licensed social worker. i dealt with this for a long time on my own. to be made to believe that i was crazy and to have him manipulate people in my life to think that i was the problem in his life. —
this morning i went back to the doctor for answers. when i had my head slammed against the wall, i had faced a minor concussion and fractured a few facial bones which also caused problems with my vision in my right eye. after x-rays it had showed that my bones didn’t properly heal and tore something in my right eye which caused the blurriness. —
well, in february i am getting corrective surgery to help repair my right eye. i go back to my counselor to relive and rehash this nightmare later this week. i finally have an answer to the cause of both of my emotional and physical pain. i was burdened with this secret in what happened to me. physically i will be healed but emotionally it will take time.

text:
i have a confession! fear has already tried to paralyze me and we're only seven days into 2019😳

i know i'm suppose to be excited and ready to ”take on the world”, but honestly, i find myself full of doubt and fear. 
reason being, i'm preparing to do something that i've never done before. something that i think will help my sisters in christ who have been sexually abused and help them move toward freedom in christ. 
so, as i'm preparing, researching, praying, and thinking about what's needed, fear and doubt has crept in.

so how do i fight against my feelings of fear? with the word!! “be strong and courageous, do not be afraid or tremble at them, for the lord your god is the one who goes with you. he will not fail you or forsake you” ‭‭deuteronomy‬ ‭31:6‬ ‭

i typically try to remain as neutral as possible when it comes to controversial topics such as this, but i feel the need to “speak out!” when it comes to sexual abuse against children, women, and yes, even men. no one should suffer at the hands of an abuser. however, this issue regarding r. kelly has shaken me to the core because i’ve been saying he’s a pedophile for almost 20 years when someone i know showed me clips of the video in question. my first response was for them to turn it off, and i then asked the question of how old that little girl was. since then, i have been boycotting his music and anything else related to him. now, i’m happy (and saddened) about the women who are courageous enough to tell their stories of abuse by r. kelly. 
i, too, have been a victim of sexual, mental, and emotional abuse within the church (from the pulpit to my former spouse), and i think it is important to use platforms like this to “speak out!” against all of it. there may be someone out there too afraid to let their voice be heard due to fear of judgment...or even fear for their life. so, i stand in solidarity with all survivors because it happened to #metoo.
#tallenspeaks

this is a photo of my ex-boyfriend. in october 2018 i ended a 4 year long abusive relationship. my life changed drastically in a 1000 ways. some negative. some positive. all for a reason. my new years resolution is to talk about it. i have been too scared, embarrassed and forbidden to do that. i want to share my story and hear yours. i want to help others heal while also healing myself. i want to live my life freely and focus on the things that matter most with less distractions. be in the moment. time is precious. don’t waste it with the wrong people.

text:
안희정성폭력사건공동대책위는 미투운동과함께하는시민행동, 민주사회를위한변호사모임 여성인권위원회와 함께 1월 14일 (월) <위력에 의한 성폭력, 판단기준은 무엇인가?>를 개최합니다. .
.
해당 토론회에서는 안희정 성폭력사건을 중심으로 지난 1심 재판부의 위력 판단의 전반적인 문제점과 개별 공소사실에 대한 판단의 문제점을 짚고, 
행위수단으로서의 현행법상의 위력과 우월적 지위에 의한 범죄 관련한 해외 입법례 검토를 통해 
현행 위력 성폭력의 판단기준의 문제점을 짚어보고 피해의 맥락을 반영한 ‘정의로운 판단기준’을 논의하는 장을 마련하고자 합니다.

많은 관심 부탁드립니다. .

text:
f r e e d o m

traditionally, prayer flags are used to promote peace, compassion, strength, and wisdom. the flags do not carry prayers to gods, which is a common misconception; rather, the tibetans believe the prayers and mantras will be blown by the wind to spread the good will and compassion into all pervading space.

when i first heard about human trafficking my heart broke. i was a junior in high school. my small town, small minded world shattered. with a group of similarly affected individuals we started a community project to raise awareness and funds so that those enslaved could have hope.

as #humantraffickingawarenessday approaches, take a few minutes to think about how much your freedom means to you. then, consider how you can instill peace, practice compassion, give strength, and pass wisdom. maybe it’s using your own voice and talents to spread awareness about human trafficking. maybe it’s using your resources to help fight this unfathomable injustice. whatever it may be, let it be done in love, because every life is beautiful and worth fighting for.

if you want to learn more about how you can fight human trafficking visit lovejustice.ngo (@lovejusticeintl)

text:
*actor kevin spacey se declarará inocente de acusación de agresión sexual a joven*

por nate raymond 
nantucket, eeuu (reuters) - el exprotagonista de "house of cards" kevin spacey compareció el lunes ante un tribunal de massachusetts para enfrentar la acusación de haber abusado sexualmente de un joven de 18 años tras atiborrarlo de alcohol en un bar en nantucket hace más de dos años.

el actor ganador del oscar no hizo un acuerdo para declararse culpable con la corte de distrito de nantucket tras ser acusado el mes pasado de un delito por abuso y agresión. 
spacey dijo en documentos judiciales que planea declararse no culpable.

vestido de traje gris y corbata, spacey no habló durante la corta audiencia previa al juicio. un juez le ordenó no contactar a su supuesta víctima.

nantucket, una isla turística costa afuera de massachusetts que usualmente es tranquila a comienzos de enero, estaba llena de camiones de cadenas de televisión el lunes.

el actor de 59 años es uno de decenas de hombres de los sectores empresarial, de la política y el entretenimiento que han sido acusados de conductas sexuales inapropiadas desde que las acusaciones contra el productor cinematográfico harvey weinstein en 2017 dieron origen al movimiento #metoo.

spacey se vio envuelto en una gran controversia después de que el actor anthony rapp lo acusó en octubre de 2017 de intentar seducirlo en 1986, cuando rapp tenía 14 años.

el actor se disculpó con rapp por su conducta inapropiada. la controversia llevó a que spacey, ganador del oscar en 2000 por su papel en "american beauty", saliera de la serie de netflix "house of cards", así como de la película "all the money in the world". el actor kevin spacey (al centro en la imagen) en la corte de distrito de nantucket en nantucket, eeuu, ene 7, 2019. 
reuters

la acusación de nantucket se conoció por vez primera en noviembre de 2017, por medio de la experiodista televisiva de boston heather unruh, que dijo a reporteros que spacey manoseó a su hijo adolescente el 7 de julio de 2016 en el restaurante y bar club car, donde trabajaba como camarero.
el hijo de unruh dijo a la policía que spacey le invitó a varias rondas de cerveza y whisky

text:
can’t think of a better way to kick off 2019 than getting this tattoo. it has been a little over a year since i was raped by someone i thought to be my best friend. and to be totally honest, getting through the last year has been the hardest thing i’ve ever done. .
.
.
anyone who knows me knows i hate when people ask the meaning behind my tattoos (or any tattoos for that matter). but i’ve found that the more i talk about what happened, the less power it has over me.  i won’t go into detail about the symbolism behind this piece, but i wanted my voice to finally join the chorus of badass survivors coming forward. while i cannot change the past, i can shape how i move forward, and am finally ready to speak up. .
.
.
thank you to my amazing friends and family for your support over the last year. and thank you @natashiaartmuse for designing this monumental custom piece for me. 💕 #metoo #survivorstory #tattoo #floraltattoo #rosemary #eglantinerose #sternumtattoo #resilience #strength #believesurvivors #believewomen

repost @falamananaosecale resistência: a história de sabrina bittencourt

olá manxs desse brasil! hoje a nossa dr vai ser sobre essa mulher que é uma ativista, que superou arduamente seus traumas, e tornou-se um símbolo de resistência na luta contra o assédio sexual feminino.
.
sabrina de campos bittencourt, teve uma infância marcada por abusos, desde seus 4 anos de idade sofreu violência sexual, por integrantes da igreja que ela frequentava com seus pais (mórmon), aos 16 ficou grávida de um de seus algozes, mas abortou! .
ela diz: “é algo endêmico essa absurda quantidade de líderes de várias religiões que abusam de crianças, jovens e, principalmente, mulheres. desde os quatro anos fui abusada diversas vezes pelos mórmons da igreja que frequentávamos, contra os quais não foi tomada nenhuma providência. o meu caminho foi traçado a partir da dor do outro e da minha dor. eu sabia desde sempre que tinha privilégios que outros não tinham. então, para poder me curar dessas dores, fiz trabalho social intensamente por 20 anos.”
.

i was in an abusive relationship that robbed me of my identity. i realized i need to find out who i am. 
what do i like, what do i want to do with my life, what are my boundaries, what do i stand for?
although it was hell going though it and it is still a healing process everyday, it’s made me stronger and still is. i’m still learning and finding myself and i’ve really embraced the idea of being true to yourself.
fitting in is boring, i want my life to be unique and be mine. everything we’ve  done in our lives has gotten us to where we are today, that means we have the power to change and create what we want for ourselves. it’s time to take up space, set boundaries and take the time to recharge and recreate! ❤️#breakthesilence #womensupportingwomen 🎨 (art by @subliming.jpg

text:
her statement: thank you, governor haslam, for your act of mercy in giving me a second chance. i will do everything i can to justify your faith in me.
i want to thank those at the tennessee department of corrections who saw something in me worth salvaging, especially ms. connie seabrooks for allowing me to participate in the lipscomb life program. it changed my life. i am also grateful to those at the tennessee department of corrections who will work with me over the next several months to help me in the transition from prison to the free world.
thank you to dr. richard goode and dr. kate watkins and all of you at lipscomb university for opening up a whole new world for me. i have one course left to finish my bachelor’s degree, which i will complete in may 2019.
i am thankful for all the support, prayers, and encouragement i have received. we truly serve a god of second chances and new beginnings. the lord has held my hand this whole time and i would have never made it without him. let today be a testament to his saving grace.
thank you to my family for being a backbone these past 14 years.
i am thankful to my lawyers and their staffs, and all the others who, for the last decade have freely given of their time and expertise to help me get to this day.
i love all of you and will be forever grateful.
with god’s help, i am committed to live the rest of my life helping others, especially young people.
my hope is to help other young girls avoid ending up where i have been.
thank you

text:
~lotus or padma mudra~
i find this mudra to have an immediate calming effect. it is related to the throat area of the body and is for communication and relaxation. it can be combined with deep breathing. when i practice it, i immediately drop into a still place of calm. ✔️position the hands near the heart and throat area
✔️place the hands together palms touching and fingers pointing upward.
✔️then spread the fingers of all the middle fingers
✔️maintain the pinky and the thumbs connected
✔️sit in a comfortable posture
✔️combine with deep breathing
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
his favorites by kate walbert ⭐️⭐️⭐️(3)
tw: sexual assault
•
though a quick read, this novel was one of the heaviest i read all year. in a small new england prep school, one of the most beloved teachers has relationships with his young teenage students. the story is one told time and time again especially in the era of #metoo and while walbert undoubtedly tackles a painful topic, she could have taken even more of a deep dive into the trauma of her protagonist. when writing about sexual assault, one needs to get under the surface and more accurately portray the long-lasting damage assault has on its victims. an interesting take, walbert could have done more here.

text:
this is @chris messina, the inventor of the #hashtag, or the method in which we use the pound sign to tag topics instead of people or profiles. he visited our studio today for an interview for anc’s news now, and i couldn’t help but run back to the newsroom and get a photo taken.

i’m such a huge fan of the hashtag because i used to think it was so novel and gimmicky, but it later turned out to be such a powerful tool. from random words bunched together, to newlyweds using this as a creative way of connecting and collecting photos, to events doing the same, and companies using it as a marketing tool, to eventually becoming a way to spark discussion about movements that are changing the world (#metoo #prayforindonesia #jesuicharlie #icebucketchallenge and so much more). it’s become so much bigger than when it first started and that’s just amazing.

okay, sorry, #fanboy moment over.
(wish i could’ve been the one to interview him but of course wishful thinking lang yun haha)

text:
tension i, 2013, collage and marker on bristol, 12”x12”

i made this piece a long time ago but have never been able to talk about it. it’s extremely personal. i’m not sure if i will ever be able to discuss details fully in a digital format. i went through something that seriously altered the state of my mind. it’s my #metoo moment so to speak. the only way i’m able to express the feelings about the trauma is through collage. by using borrowed images from older fashion magazines, i’m able to remove myself from a presence that will forever follow my life. i am a product of my environment. i cannot escape the past. i can only move on. some things are meant to be shared. some things aren’t. they’re meant to be figured out. share your experiences because knowledge is power. but also understand that everyone has their own story, and they can choose what they want to do with it.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#atlanta #atlantaartist #bodypositive #bodypositivity #collageart #collage #mixedmedia #oldisnew #writingisart2

text:
i am a survivor of sexual and physical abuse from the age of 7 to 35. most women that endured what i have would be insane, on drugs, in jail or dead. i am thankful for my relationship with jesus christ. god is my sanity. christ is my endurance. and because of the torture i've endured ; i decided to pour out my life and the grace and strength god has given me to overcome. that's why i'm writing my books. the country is upset,( and it's about time) for what these girls endured for a short time. i've overcome nearly a life time of abuse at the hands of men...and still open my heart to love. i have yet to be loved truly...but there is always tomorrow. i will never lose faith that god will bring me that joy. as long as we keep telling our stories and standing up against these sick men... that's what matters.
.
.
 #muterkelly #metoo #timesup #girlup #girlboss #girlpower #empoweringwomen #singlemomstrong #singlemomlife #blacklivesmatter #rkelly

text:
r. kelly's music sales have increased since the airing of 'surviving r. kelly', but why? our panelist will unpack this during a live facebook roundtable discussion: how can we stop failing black women and girls.

join us on wednesday, january 9th at 9pm est.

our panelist includes:
teresa baker, political consultant, author of josie's bedazzled shoes and ceo/founder of @brownboybrowngirl. their mission is to empower and inspire brown boys and brown girls through reading while helping parents to raise children who see the beauty of their true selves.

christopher everage edgar-smith, llmsw, clinical therapist specializing in addiction treatment with a trauma-focused lense.

@yusefbunchyshakur author of the window 2 my soul, my soul looks back and scribes of redemption. a neighborhood organizer, activist, social entrepreneur and documentary filmmaker, shakur is co-director of programs at the michigan roundtable for diversity and inclusion.
.

text:
binge-watched “surviving r. jelly” today and all i can say in short is “wow.” i typically stay far away from the drama of celebrities, but as someone who has dreams of working in public relations in the music industry with an obsession of music & lyrics, i was undeniably intrigued to hear these stories i was reading about on fb. it’s hard to imagine that a monster like that presently lives among us - as in is currently breathing the same air we do & is currently active in his crimes. not only that, but he actively pursues his criminal acts in plain sight. i was guilty of not being aware of his current sins & ignoring his previous ones, continuing to separate the art from the artist. but this must stop. he can not continue to be allowed to prey on our daughters. i watched the final episode while my daughter played next to me & all i wanted to do was hold her tight. i can’t imagine what these parents went & are currently going through. i send my prayers out to them & out to their daughters, so that they may get up the courage to finally remove themselves from his imprisonment. 
please people....as a society, we must protect our children from these predators. we have allowed our musicians, actors, athletes, etc to get away with much too much! we have to connect as a community & put a stop to it. stop allowing your children out of your reach, stop allowing them to think no one loves them, stop allowing these monsters to live & breathe in plain sight, cloaked in celebrity & fame...suffocate them by lack of support. it’s #timesup for these bastards....#muterkelly so we can #mutethemall. #blackgirlsmatter #metoo #survivingrkelly

text:
it has become very apparent that there is a major racial divide on topics that involve sexual violence against black women. particularly in the wake of the lifetime docu-series highlighting the overt predatory nature of r.kelly.

the silence of our so-called intersectional white allies that is deafening and very noticeable.

however- i honestly don’t believe it’s complicity or lack of caring this time- it feels like a case where white feminists, particularly white women don’t know what to do. they are afraid of crossing the line. they are afraid black women don’t want their support. they are afraid they will accidentally center themselves, when the true aim is simply solidarity. i get that.

while it is not the job of bipoc to educate, it is our job to tell people how they can help us. we all recognize allyship can often be unguided making good intentions go in the wrong direction. allyship can be full of criticism, making you feel like you are damned if you do, damned if you don’t. i also know without proper awareness, allyship can’t be optimized.

we don’t need any other divides between humanity. we must find a way to work together, in harmony, with integrity, and with inclusivity as our foundation. white allies, rather than simply tell you what you’re not doing, let us black women tell you what you can do.

my profile temporarily contains the link to a post that includes links to actionable steps which lead to proper allyship. acting on these key things is solidarity. this is how we need you to show up. this is how you #protectblackgirls #listentoblackwomen #believeblackwomen #supportblackwomen #muterkelly and honor the #metoo and #timesup movements.

for those of you who are skimmers, i’ll include a few screenshots as a sneak peak at the excellent resources from @drtyffani & @fierceblackfemme found in my post. follow them. see the full post with resources at the link in my profile.

⁣
when was the last time you hugged someone, and held on tight and for a long time? ⁣
 #healing #radicalselfcare ⁣

text:
best friends come in many different forms. we’ve all lost people we thought would never give up on us for anything. it’s difficult to comprehend when someone you considered to be family (and even family themselves) turns their back on you. on one hand, i understand because i know they can’t stand to see someone they care about getting hurt. but on the other hand, isn’t that what makes them a best friend to begin with? in any case, i know i’ve personally lost people who i thought would never turn their backs on me, saying they’ll return if/when i leave. in all honesty, you won’t hear from me again. so you’ll be there for me when i’m all good, but not when i need you the most? no thanks. •

text:
today was one of those days where i struggled to get out of bed as a certain little child was fighting bed time last night and was still screaming the house down after midnight, then once she was 'asleep' she began roaming the house talking to herself,  it was well after 3am before i got to shut my eyes. so after doing a clean out and dump run we headed down the coast to this pretty piece of paradise, lunch on the beach, and a dip in the river. such a beautiful, calm' and quiet spot, perfect for tara. she just casually strolled straight across the river, low tide of course and splashed her way back. some days things just don't go to plan, and you just have to go with it, and it turned out to be a pretty cool day, and found this beauty full of nature's sea creatures. one day at a time.

text:
cw: rape, sexual assault

tonight marks the second anniversary of when a person, who i will only refer to as “lg”, raped me. i’ll never forget his sunken eyes, the smell of his onion-tinged tongue, or the feeling of his drooling teeth on my body. and you know what? i don’t want to forget. i can’t forget, i obviously can’t forgive, and part of me is shocked that i’ve made it this far. i’m so thankful for everyone who’s supported me over these past two years, and i’m especially thankful to some movies that have helped me cope, some of which have provided the most unexpected solace.
.
- under the skin, dir. jonathan glazer - the feeling of wanting to take your skin off after the experience. the feeling of the inside looking at the outside before floating into the stratosphere.
- the neon demon, dir. nicolas winding refn - the destruction of the line between ravishing a person and ruining them. oddly enough, i watched the film’s ending as i sat in the bath after “it” happened to me.
- jennifer’s body, dir. karyn kusama - the fast-talking, seemingly cool guy who’s nothing but a succubus, and the irrevocable damages he can cause. also the film with one of the most satisfying end credits scenes i can think of.
- eighth grade, dir. bo burnham - the age difference, the exploitation of naïveté, and the gaslighting when it doesn’t totally go his way.
- mother!, dir. darren aronofsky - the horror when one person’s giving turns into another person’s taking.
- revenge, dir. coralie fargeat - sometimes bathing in the blood of the world’s scum is the most cleansing thing there is.
- bongo cat memes - it may sound weird, but it’s the best kind of white noise. it’s adorable. if only we could all be as pure as bongo cat.

thank you.

sunday, january 8, 2017, 3:41 am cst. i have to acknowledge it. it’d be a lie not to. #metoo

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
a few months later, in autumn 2013, wylie met steve bannon. at the time, he was editor-in-chief of breitbart, which he had brought to britain to support his friend nigel farage in his mission to take britain out of the european union.

what was he like? - smart, says wylie. - interesting. really interested in ideas. he’s the only straight man i’ve ever talked to about intersectional feminist theory. he saw its relevance straightaway to the oppressions that conservative, young white men feel.

wylie meeting bannon was the moment petrol was poured on a flickering flame. wylie lives for ideas. he speaks 19 to the dozen for hours at a time. he had a theory to prove. and at the time, this was a purely intellectual problem. politics was like fashion, he told bannon.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
“the storm is coming,” say the conspiracy theorizers whose grotesque imaginings terrified the country to attention this week. maybe they’re right.

the simplest description of the plot line goes something like this: president trump isn’t under investigation; he is only pretending to be, as part of a countercoup to restore power to the people after more than a century of governmental control by a globalist cabal. also, there are pedophiles.

a figure named “q,” who supposedly possesses q-level security clearance, disperses “crumbs” that “bakers” bring together to create a “dough” of synthesized information. (this is not how baking works, but that seems the least of our worries.) because q is the 17th letter in the alphabet and 17 is also a number trump has said a few times, among other clearly-not-coincidences, he is the real deal, not an internet troll engaged in an elaborate example of live-action role-play.

that’s what qanon followers really want, after all. that’s where their “storm” motto comes from. most americans were puzzled when, in a meeting with military leaders months ago, trump said, “you know what this represents? maybe it’s the calm before the storm.” but these theorists thought they knew exactly what he was talking about. trump was pointing at the officers’ uniforms.

the storm qanon truthers predict will never strike because the conspiracy that obsesses them doesn’t exist. but while they wait for it, they’ll try to whip up the winds, and the rest of us will struggle to find shelter. qanon is scary because it’s getting bigger, it’s scary because we don’t know how to stop it, and it’s scary because the people behind it won’t be stopped, and, until their illusory storm arrives, they won’t be satisfied.

molly roberts
the washington post

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
cyntoia brown. we stan.

thank you @governorbillhaslam for doing the right thing and granting full clemency to #cyntoniabrown. believe victims. trust victims.

imagine serving 15 years of a life sentence for a degree murder, felony murder and aggravated robbery for being a victim of child sex trafficking and defending yourself. she killed her abuser rightfully.

she is set to be released from prison august 7th on time served and will remain on parole for 10 years.

this is also a reminder that the system is still messed up and we, the public, have a duty to call it out. she should never have been imprisoned in the first place. 🗣‼️📣#yoursistersspace

text: people get defensive when you talk about class or wealth and mental illness. i learned this earlier this week when i found myself embroiled in a twitter debate over “the class issue.” i did something unusual for me, and replied to a tweet stating that being middle class doesn’t lessen depression. i responded saying that i believe class is really critical to our dialogue about mental health: “being middle class and having a safety net can give you a better chance at recovery… my safety net benefited me immensely. financial help allowed me to get therapy. it meant when i couldn’t physically work that was ok.” and then something interesting happened. i started receiving defensive replies. one person told me financial advantage is just “more noise”: it doesn’t change anything, they claimed. someone else told me there’s no point talking about the “class issue” when someone’s on fire. but we do need to talk about the class issue – because it has a huge impact on how we make mental health recovery accessible to all. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2019/01/08/we-cannot-ignore-wealth-and-class-when-we-talk-about-mental-illness/ #metoo #youwillbearwitness #ptsd #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #ptsdawareness #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #trauma #dissociativeidentitydisorder #therapydog #doitfordolly

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters
