text:
#transparenttuesday my blog is my life story starting in 2013. there are times when it’s insanely dramatic, crazy emotional, and dark... but keep in mind this isn’t a netflix series (even though it seems like it)😂 it isn’t always going to be dramatic and binge-worthy!
- although i still had my struggles, after 2015 my life became a lot brighter and happier. my future blog posts will most likely not be as dramatic as before... but they will still hold great value as i have learned so many things since having hudson that i know will be beneficial for all of you💕
- i decided to share my story for all of the girls out there like me who felt alone, unworthy, or depressed. for all the girls who didn’t know if they could make it over the bump in the road. and for all the girls who thought their future was over. my hope has and always will be to help you!💗 - thank you to all of you who started this journey with me and have continued to follow my story despite the lack of crazy drama in recent posts!✨ it means the world to me to hear from you and see you guys sharing my story with others! much love to all of you💘

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

…and boom tank jumps in to the conversation. this is a good thing. lately conversations have brought black men in r&b to the forefront. from jaquees saying is the modern day king of r&b (… the jury is still out on that), to r kelly being exposed on lifetime. tank is right, we can’t excuse it. we have to be advocates for what’s right. let’s face it. some of these allegations are old. r kelly has been the pee pee king! what’s different is people actually getting to tell their story. yeah there is a lot floating around about black men and their careers being destroyed, but lets be real here… if they do wrong they should be punished. especially sexual crimes. people always resort to the argument of powerful white men not getting in trouble. everyday black people work to contrast ourselves from the hateful actions of some whites. why would we use them to justify wrong? lets hold our people accountable even if others don’t! 
what are your thoughts?

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text_retweet:
regardless what’s said in ya news outlets, fake or not, there is no greater honor then this my man. never sexual, but mind body soul spiritual. any real playa, “christ jesus” carpenter lessons, just want to show off for their ladies in a unseen special way...all secrets voided. me too movements abolished...because as a real man, beginning with the drug trade as a child, they got “me too.” now you know this day and age team us gotta get em. any questions??? a.o.w.l. #metoo #londonfog #resurrection #madeinamerica #thegods #christjesus #carpenters #rewarded #realart #attraction #artofwarlifestyle *repost* @brian_freschi with @get_repost
・・・
“@freedoflondon è per prima cosa un'azienda... ma di che cosa si occupa?
semplice, di creare scarpette per ballerini completamente a mano, senza mostruose apparecchiature a catena di montaggio che sbuffano e ruttano tutto il tempo. l'arte della leggendaria freed of london è nata dal sogno di frederick freed, quando aveva solo tre strumenti e tanta passione per creare e personalizzare le scarpe da punta di ogni singola ballerina. la manifattura delle scarpette dura ben due giorni! due giorni in cui gli artigiani prima costruiscono il blocco che sta alla base della scarpa (dall'interno verso l'esterno), poi rivestono il tutto con raso, asciugano e cuciono le solette... dopodiché infornano e lasciano a riposo per una notte. l'azienda ha non uno, non due, ma più di venti artigiani e artisti internazionali provenienti da ogni angolo del mondo... tutti pronti a lasciare un segno indelebile su ogni singola scarpetta a punta e tutti pronti a seguire il metodo freed come fosse il verbo di un guru intramontabile. le “cose” possono essere opere d’arte uniche, pensate per chi l’arte la fa!”
di nuovo al lavoro con @carotecannella e @unifirenze!
.
.
.

text:
new to the consent tents instagram is a collection on #healthyrelationships. these relationships can include romantic relationships and platonic relationships.⠀
the aim is to think about yours and your partners behaviours in different settings and challenge whether they are healthy behaviours or not.⠀
every relationship is different, therefore only you will be able to know which boundaries work for you.⠀
boundaries are all about respect... and consent! you and your partner should know what is too far in all aspects of your relationship so that both of you feel safe.⠀
digital dating abuse is the use of technologies such as texting and social networking to bully, harass, stalk or intimidate a partner. often this behaviour is a form of verbal or emotional abuse perpetrated online.⠀
in a healthy relationship, all communication is respectful whether in person, online or by phone. it is never okay for someone to do or say anything that makes you feel bad, lowers your self-esteem or manipulates you. ⠀
⠀
an organisation that has more information on this is @loveisrespectofficial.⠀
⠀

the january theme is here! and honestly it’s been a long time coming. this month out theme is #metoo: stories of survival and resistance. #metoo has been all over social media for a while. but we think it’s time for us to tell some of your stories. you can find all the submission details in the link in our bio. || the art work for this month’s theme was done by @bysarahmessina. we are so excited that sarah will be illustrating the 2019 monthly themes which will all be for sale in the herstry marketplace. this month we are donating a dollar from ever sale of our #metoo print to @endthebacklog, a nonprofit working to end the rape kit backlog in the us (thanks @myfavoritemurder for bringing them to our attention). so hurry! get your stories in (due jan 25th) and grab your own copy of the january print and let’s help end the backlog and get those rape kits tested. .
.
.
.
.
.

text:
we all think we are in charge of our own lives, right?
•
what about all your beliefs? •
like many others, i used to believe that i wasn't good enough, smart enough, pretty enough.... just....enough!
•
at the core, i believed i wasn't capable of any better because i didn't deserve any better.
•
so, was i really the captain of my own ship, or was i letting my beliefs, due to the words and actions of someone else, guide my way?
•
thankfully, i got real. i looked long and hard at my beliefs, challenged them, and then re-wrote the script.
•
now, i really am in charge of me! i'm an active participant in my life and i make conscious decisions every single day to keep myself on my path - to grow and heal, and continue to love and cherish myself.
•
are you ready to do the same?
•

•
